k = 1.5

q1_1st = np.percentile(all_data['Curricular units 1st sem (grade)'], 25)
q3_1st = np.percentile(all_data['Curricular units 1st sem (grade)'], 75)
iqr_1st = q3_1st - q1_1st
lower_bound_1st = q1_1st - k * iqr_1st
upper_bound_1st = q3_1st + k * iqr_1st

q1_2nd = np.percentile(all_data['Curricular units 2nd sem (grade)'], 25)
q3_2nd = np.percentile(all_data['Curricular units 2nd sem (grade)'], 75)
iqr_2nd = q3_2nd - q1_2nd
lower_bound_2nd = q1_2nd - k * iqr_2nd
upper_bound_2nd = q3_2nd + k * iqr_2nd

# Identify and remove the outliers
filtered_data = all_data[(all_data['Curricular units 1st sem (grade)'] >= lower_bound_1st) & (all_data['Curricular units 1st sem (grade)'] <= upper_bound_1st) & (all_data['Curricular units 2nd sem (grade)'] >= lower_bound_2nd) & (all_data['Curricular units 2nd sem (grade)'] <= upper_bound_2nd)]

# Create a scatter plot with the filtered data
fig, ax = plt.subplots()

In [80]:
# Define the threshold multiplier
k = 1.5

# Calculate the IQR and the bounds for each numerical column
bounds = {}
for col in num_cols:
    q1 = np.percentile(all_data[col], 25)
    q3 = np.percentile(all_data[col], 75)
    iqr = q3 - q1
    lower_bound = q1 - k * iqr
    upper_bound = q3 + k * iqr
    bounds[col] = (lower_bound, upper_bound)

# Identify and remove the outliers from each numerical column
filtered_data = all_data.copy()
for col in num_cols:
    filtered_data = filtered_data[(filtered_data[col] >= bounds[col][0]) & (filtered_data[col] <= bounds[col][1])]

# Create a scatter matrix plot with the filtered data
pd.plotting.scatter_matrix(filtered_data[num_cols], figsize=(20, 20))

# Set the title of the plot
plt.suptitle('2.3.2 Scatter Matrix of Six Numerical Variables (without outliers)', size=16)

# Show the plot
plt.show()
